  "_comment": "Canonical musical-works registry — the SINGLE source of truth for (1) tradition tag, (2) cross-language de-dup, (3) bilingual display. One entry per work: `canonical` (English/original display name), `tradition` (Broadway/West End | 德奧音樂劇 | 法式音樂劇 | 日本原創 | 台灣原創 | 韓國原創 | 歐陸原創), and `aliases` (every OTHER title the work appears under across sources/languages). build_shows.py normalises canonical+aliases with group_key and indexes them, so any alias resolves to the same group + tradition + bilingual prefix. Only works needing this are listed: those with a NON-default tradition (anything but Broadway/West End) OR a non-English alias. Plain English-titled Anglo shows are omitted — they default to Broadway/West End. To add coverage: append the work once with all its language variants. Discovery report (build_shows --discover) lists local-source titles that look like unmapped imports.",
